# SHRINE Coding Standards

## Architecture
- **Clean Architecture**: Separate concerns - types, providers, hooks, components, API
- **DRY Principle**: No duplicated logic. Use abstractions.
- **Strategy Pattern**: All AI providers implement a common interface.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled. No `any` types.
- All functions must have explicit return types.
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/aliases.
- Export types from `types/` directory.

## Components
- Use functional components with explicit prop interfaces.
- Colocate hooks with their consuming components when single-use.
- Shared hooks go in `hooks/` directory.

## Streaming
- Always use streaming for AI responses (ReadableStream or Vercel AI SDK).
- Never use blocking `fetch` for AI calls.

## Error Handling
- Every AI provider call must have graceful error handling.
- UI must show degradation state per-model, never crash entirely.

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes.
- Follow Shrine design tokens: zinc-950 bg, amber-400 accents.
- Use Framer Motion for animations.
- ShadcnUI for base components.
